            <div align="center">
                <h2>BOOK COLLECTION DRIVE</h2>
                <br />
                <div class="border_image">
                    <p>
                        Book Collection Drives are organised with much zeal and zest by all 
                            campus units of Leaders for Tomorrow. The event helps the campus leaders, 
                            members and volunteers understand the importance of sharing knowledge and equip as many people as possible with the weapon of information for the development of our nation.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        As a part of this event- which is backed by a huge publicity campaign on campus, through hand made posters, SMS, emails and announcements- cartons were set up in various prominent students joints with our logo and tags where students were encouraged to drop old story books and general knowledge books so that the volunteers could distribute among those who needed it.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        As a follow up activity, the collected books are categorised into various sections such as – science, fairy tales, moral books etc and donated to various shelters and schools for the lesser privileged; especially those that were seeking to build libraries or didn’t have any provision for such exposure.
                    </p>
                    <a href="#">Album</a>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div align="center">
                <h2>VISIT FOR COMPASSION</h2>
                <br />
                <div class="border_image">
                    <p>
                        LFT Leaders visit shelter homes and other ngos to spend time with those who live
                        there. This is to ignite the social consciousness in the youth and also to instill
                        in them the values of compassion.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        The volunteers and leaders play games, read stories and participate in the daily
                        activities of the NGO they visit for a few hours as a part of this programme.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Often the shelter homes visited through this programmes are also beneficiaries of
                        our collection drives.
                    </p>
                    <a href="#">Album</a>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div align="center">
                <h2>BE THE LEADER</h2>
                <br />
                <div class="border_image">
                    <p>
                        We at Leaders For Tomorrow believe that it is not enough to just ask the youth to
                        find the hidden leader in them. They must also be trained in leading social change.
                        Thus, we engage our leaders and volunteers in ‘Be The Leader’ Programme that focuses
                        on Youth Advocacy.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        The programme is headed by our college campus leaders across all major colleges
                        of Delhi University and IP University. During the programme, they go to different
                        classrooms and prominent places on campus to interact with them on the need for
                        youth to get involved in social change.
                    </p>
